<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{2}{y}={52}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3}{x}-{2}{y}={11}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{2}{y}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={52}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{52}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{\left(\frac{{{52}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}\right)}+-{2}{y}={11}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{3}}{{6}}\cdot{\left({52}\right)}-\frac{{3}}{{6}}{\left({2}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}={11}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{26}-{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}={11}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}={11}-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{y}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{15}}{{-{{3}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{2}{\left({5}\right)}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{\left({10}\right)}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={52}-{\left({10}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{42}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

